############################################
############### FUNCTIONING ################
############################################


0)  COMMANDS
    javac *.java // compiling the whole project
    java Server // running server side
    java Publisher // running client side

1)  Server is launched (Server Class) and listens to the network.

2)  Client is launched (Publish Class) and a Request object is created
    with a header and a body and some others info.
    // TODO dedezdzedze - PS: if Follower Class is launched, there is no Request object, but only a String object

3)  The server receives the data from the client (String object, from ByteBuffer)
    and analyzes it to recreate a Request object.
    At the same time, the server adds the info of request to the database (if needed).
    Database Class allows to handle data (messages, etc.) retrieved from Persistence files
    (PersistenceMsg and PersistenceSubcription).

4)  The server prepares an answer according ProcessingData Claass.

5) The server sends the answer to the client.

